Find Confidence Intervals

use t.test() function to find confidence intervals (for one sample) and perform t-tests to compare means of two samples

## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  ivee_lobsters
## t = 245.23, df = 2302, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  72.99130 74.16806
## sample estimates:
## mean of x 
##  73.57968

2 sample t-test to compare means

is there a significant difference in lobster lengths at Naples and Mohawk reefs?

weve done our necessary exploratory analyses (sample size large, normal distribution for both samples) to determine that a 2-sample t-test for means comparison is appropriate

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  mohk_sample and napl_sample
## t = -19.849, df = 1850.8, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -12.43436 -10.19806
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  66.86833  78.18454

There is a significant difference in lobster lengths between Naples and Mohawk Reef (t(df) = statistic, p < 0.001, alpha =0.05).
